                  </hi>.** <hi rend="italic">He was further charged with having been before con<lb></lb>victed, at Newington, on the 31st July, 1863, in the name of <persName id="t18670610-name-561">
                        <interp inst="t18670610-name-561" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18670610-name-561" type="surname" value="ETTLE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18670610-name-561" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>William Ettle</persName>, to which he</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
PLEADED GUILTY</hi>.—<hi rend="italic">
